headline.main: ACE GIVES CREDIT TO FLYING 'TEAM'; Captain Foss of Marines, Who Bagged 26 Japanese Planes, Hails 7 Fellow Fliers 4 'FARM BOYS' EXCELLED But Three 'City Slickers' in the Group Got 5 or More Craft -- Foe's Pilots Capable

lead_paragraph: Captain Joseph J. Foss, outstanding Marine Corps flier, who shot down twenty-six Japanese planes in ten weeks of action over Guadalcanal, attributed his success yesterday to the teamwork of the seven other pilots of his "Flying Circus," which he said consisted of "four farmers and four city slickers."
abstract: repts Jap pilots competent and planes good
